<FlowDocument xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml/presentation"  TextAlignment="Justify"   xmlns:x="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml">

<Paragraph>Essential Presentation library has support for manipulating SmartArt in a PowerPoint presentation.</Paragraph>
<Paragraph>This sample demonstrates how to add/remove nodes in a SmartArt diagram and edit text of the nodes in a PowerPoint presentation.</Paragraph>
<BlockUIContainer>
<TextBlock Style="{DynamicResource HeaderTextStyle}"><Bold>Features:</Bold></TextBlock>
</BlockUIContainer>
<List>
<ListItem><Paragraph>Add and remove nodes in an existing SmartArt diagram.</Paragraph></ListItem>
<ListItem><Paragraph>Edit text contents of the SmartArt nodes.</Paragraph></ListItem>
<ListItem><Paragraph>Make a SmartArt node as assistant node.</Paragraph></ListItem>
</List>
<Paragraph><Bold>Note1:</Bold> This library supports creation, manipulation and conversion to PDF/image for .pptx format alone.</Paragraph>
<Paragraph><Bold>Note2:</Bold> The modifications in a SmartArt diagram (like add/remove nodes, modify position and size of nodes etc., which involve SmartArt layout changes) done by Essential Presentation are not supported in Image and PDF conversion. Whereas layout changes will be reflected properly in the generated PPTX file when opened using Microsoft PowerPoint.</Paragraph>
